review_blob: Brazilian version brewed by Anbev. Light colored, pleasant sweet after taste. 5% alcohol, more than adequate for a tropical climate area.
Brazilian Pilsen. Very acid as many other Brazilian Pilsen beers. Almost no bitterness due to very small amount of hop and non malted cereals like corn and rice.
Brazilian version, 4.6%, sweet after taste. Pleasant colour. Perfect for a tropical climate due to its reduced alcohol percentage.
Delicious lager. Right balance between bitterness and sweetness. Proper amount of hop.
